HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 116
BY REPRESENTATIVE WYBLE
COMMENDATIONS: Commends the Ben's Ford Christian School girls basketball team
on winning the Midsouth Association of Independent Schools 2026 Class 3A state
championship
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend the Ben's Ford Christian School girls basketball team on winning the Midsouth
3 Association of Independent Schools (MAIS) 2026 Class 3A state championship.
4 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize the Ben's Ford Christian School girls
5 basketball team for their outstanding season and to commend the team on winning the MAIS
6 2026 Class 3A state championship; and
7 WHEREAS, Ben's Ford Christian School is a private educational institution that was
8 founded in 1983 and provides a comprehensive education rooted in Christian values; and
9 WHEREAS, this year's girls basketball team became the first team in school history
10 to play for and win a state championship; ten years ago, the girls basketball team finished
11 with a record of zero wins and twenty-five losses, and this year, the squad finished with
12 twenty-five wins and seven losses; and
13 WHEREAS, the Ben's Ford Christian School girls basketball team is led by Coaches
14 Mark McGehee and Derek Dantin, and the team's statistician is Mitchell Castleberry; and
15 WHEREAS, the members of the MAIS Class 3A state champion girls basketball
16 team are Avery Bell, Scarlet Barber, Zoe Nastasia, Abby Robichaux, Kinley Stewart,
17 Matilda Golby, Annabelle Knight, Delaney Perrette, Avery Dantin, Alivia Harrington,
18 Rebecca Cyuzuzo, Zoe Houston, and Maddie Willis; and
